The GJ 2056 Exoplanetary System


Overview

GJ 2056 is a star with 0.62 times the mass of the Sun, and NaN times its radius. It is located NaN light years away from the solar system.

GJ 2056 is known to have undefined exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the GJ 2056 system


GJ 2056 b

GJ 2056 b was discovered by the undefined observatory using the radial velocity method. Its semi-major axis is 0.28 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of GJ 2056 b is 16.20846 times the mass of Earth. The radius of GJ 2056 b is 4.17 that of Earth. At more than 10 Earth masses, GJ 2056 b is an ice giant, a planet that is made up mostly of volatiles like water, amonia and methane, and enveloped by a dense hydrogen and helium atmosphere, much like Uranus and Neptune in our solar system.
